Interview Peter Praet with Les Echos (FR)
 http://t.co/NbxWvyT6XA
Draghi: key to persevere on path of reform – within the euro area, we all benefit from each other’s prosperity.
Draghi: While cost adjustments increase relative competitiveness, productivity gains, by increasing trend growth, benefit all countries.
Draghi: competitiveness is not a race between euro area countries with winners and losers.
Draghi: closing the competitiveness gap is a key component of improving the current economic situation.
Draghi: Governments addressing fiscal policy challenges. Primary fiscal deficit for euro area fell from 3.5% of GDP in 2009 to 0.5% in 2012.

Speech Mario Draghi at Euro Conference in Latvia http://t.co/oGeRwrIYVF (en) http://t.co/tq4xIR9l1R (lv)
Draghi: I warmly welcome our 18th member. Welcome Latvia!
Draghi: I welcome the vote today by the European Parliament on the new European supervisor, the Single Supervisory Mechanism (SSM)
Draghi: The key to maintaining sovereignty in this world is to share more sovereignty by integrating more deeply
Draghi: Sustainable convergence means real convergence prior to adopting the euro but also continued efforts once inside monetary union
Draghi: Countries that join the euro area today can be confident that its central pillar, its monetary policy, is sound
Draghi: We have learned that we need to complete the institutions of our Economic and Monetary Union
Draghi: We have learned the types of policy that lead to prosperity within Monetary Union, and also the ones that do not
Draghi: We have learned the euro as a currency works
Draghi: New members of the euro area can benefit from the lessons we have learned since 1999
